Zucker Diabetic Fatty rat model was used for this study.•A 6mm biopsy punch was used to create four horizontal artificial wounds on the dorsal side of the rats.•A silicone sheet was then inserted underneath the two wounds in the center in order to induce ischemia.•Each rat received a different treatment on each side, with the two outer wounds serving as control for non-ischemic conditions.•The different treatments included:•SIS±EPC•SIS+SILY+DS±EPC•SIS+SILY+DS+LXW7±EPC•The size and condition of the wounds were monitored for 14 days•After 14 days of treatment, the rats were sacrificed, and tissue specimens were collected•The tissue were imbedded in Optimum Cutting Temperature and then cryo-sectioned at 6μm onto slides•Slides were subjected to H&E staining as well as immunofluorescent staining•The slides were then analyzed for re-epithelialization and angiogenesis
